        GET_ON_THAT_AIRSHIP_TO_BASTOK_SOLDIER_I                                 = 10184,  -- Get on that airship to Bastok, soldier! I'll stay here and find out what I can.
        SO_IT_S_BUSINESS_AS_USUAL_IN_BASTOK                                     = 10185,  -- So, it's business as usual in Bastok, huh? Well, we have nothing special for you here, so try following the administration's directives.
        THERE_YOU_ARE_GREAT_WORK                                                = 10186,  -- There you are! Great work, %!
        I_M_SORRY_BUT_YOU_VE_GOT_NO                                             = 10187,  -- I'm sorry, but you've got no time to rest! Our beloved Windurst is in grave danger!
        WITH_THE_AMBASSADOR_AWAY_I_WANT_YOU_TO                                  = 10188,  -- With the ambassador away, I want you to take this back to the motherland. Take the airship; it's faster. I'll find out what I can here.
        HURRY_SCURRY_TAKE_THE_AIRSHIP_BACK_TO_WINDURST                          = 10189,  -- Hurry-scurry! Take the airship back to Windurst! I'll find out what I can here.
        AS_LONG_AS_THE_STAR_SIBYL_IS_SAFE                                       = 10190,  -- As long as the Star Sibyl is safe, then all is well. We don't have any tasks for you here, so continue your service to your country.
        YOU_DON_T_HAVE                                                          = 10191,  -- You don't have %.
        NOBODY_SEES_THE_SOVEREIGN_WITHOUT_AN_APPOINTMENT                        = 10192,  -- Nobody sees the sovereign without an appointment!
        STAND_DOWN                                                              = 10193,  -- Stand down!
        JUST_A_MOMENT_I_NEED_TO_SEE_YOUR                                        = 10194,  -- Just a moment. I need to see your %...
        THANK_YOU_IF_THE_SOVEREIGN_REQUESTS_YOUR_AUDIENCE                       = 10195,  -- Thank you. If the sovereign requests your audience, access to the chamber will be granted by the guards inside.
        I_M_SORRY_BUT_YOU_WILL_NEED_TO                                          = 10196,  -- I'm sorry, but you will need % to get in.
        THIS_THE_HALL_OF_THE_DUCAL_GUARDS_ONLY                                  = 10197,  -- This the hall of the Ducal Guards. Only the finest warriors may join. Come to think of it, this is no place for civilians like you.
        SIR_WOLFGANG_IS_OUR_LEADER_HE_WAS_SELECTED                              = 10198,  -- Sir Wolfgang is our leader. He was selected not just for his skill at arms, but also for his unwavering determination.
        WHO_ARE_YOU_AND_WHAT_S_YOUR_BUSINESS                                    = 10199,  -- Who are you and what's your business!? Oh, you're an attach%i... My apologies! I have to check everyone who passes through here.
        IN_THIS_JOB_I_ASSUME_EVERYONE_S_GUILTY                                  = 10200,  -- In this job, I assume everyone's guilty until proven innocent. I meant no offense.
        WELCOME_THIS_IS_THE_HOME_OF_THE_ARCHDUKE                                = 10201,  -- Welcome. This is the home of the archduke, so please conduct yourself accordingly.
        LORDS_KAM_LANAUT_AND_EALD_NARCHE_RARELY_MAKE                            = 10202,  -- Lords Kam'lanaut and Eald'narche rarely make public appearances.
        AND_YOU_NEED_A_SPECIAL_PERMIT_JUST_TO                                   = 10203,  -- And you need a special permit just to have an audience with them.
        BOTH_HAVE_KEPT_THEIR_YOUTH_THROUGH_ALL_THESE                            = 10204,  -- Both have kept their youth through all these years. Perhaps some otherworldly power watches over them. Great prophets like them are few indeed!
        SAY_YOU_KNOW_ALDO_THE_GUY_WHO_RUNS                                      = 10205,  -- Say... You know Aldo, the guy who runs the organization called the Tenshodo?
        DO_YOU_KNOW_HIM_YES_NO                                                  = 10206,  -- Do you know him? Yes. No.
        THE_TENSHODO_WAS_FOUNDED_BY_ALDO_S_FATHER                               = 10207,  -- The Tenshodo was founded by Aldo's father. They've done so well in trading abroad that they own the black market in these parts. Er, so I've heard...
        ALDO_TOOK_OVER_AFTER_HIS_FATHER_DIED_I                                  = 10208,  -- Aldo took over after his father died. I've heard all kinds of things about him, but they say he's a smart and honorable man.
        OH_YOU_RE_A_TENSHODO_MEMBER_I_GUESS                                     = 10209,  -- Oh, you're a Tenshodo member? I guess you know more than I do, then.
        YOU_SHOULD_DO_BUSINESS_WITH_THE_TENSHODO_TOO                            = 10210,  -- You should do business with the Tenshodo, too. They supply us with hard-to-find goods now and then.
        BEYOND_US_STANDS_THE_PEACE_MONUMENT_CONSTRUCTED_AFTER                   = 10211,  -- Beyond us stands the peace monument, constructed after the war. The embassies were built around it.
        LORDS_KAM_LANAUT_AND_EALD_NARCHE_DESIGNED_THESE                         = 10212,  -- Lords Kam'lanaut and Eald'narche designed these gardens of Ru'Lude. One look is enough to see how much they treasure peace.
        THESE_GROUNDS_ARE_THE_DOMAIN_OF_LORDS_KAM                               = 10213,  -- These grounds are the domain of Lords Kam'lanaut and Eald'narche. Please conduct yourself properly.
        HAVE_YOU_EVER_MET_LORD_EALD_NARCHE_HE                                   = 10214,  -- Have you ever met Lord Eald'narche? He's still a lad, but the archduke's brother is gifted with incredible talents.
        JEUNO_IS_SAFE_AS_LONG_AS_IT_HAS                                         = 10215,  -- Jeuno is safe as long as it has Archduke Kam'lanaut and Lord Eald'narche.
        THE_THREE_GREAT_NATIONS_PREACH_FRIENDSHIP_BUT_BENEATH                   = 10216,  -- The three great nations preach friendship, but beneath the facade is a struggle for supremacy. Nobody can tell what will come of it.
        THAT_IS_WHY_WE_MUST_FOCUS_ON_OUR                                        = 10217,  -- That is why we must focus on our duties. There is no guarantee that the reign of peace we enjoy now will last.
        DID_YOU_KNOW_THAT_LORD_EALD_NARCHE_WEARS                                = 10218,  -- Did you know that Lord Eald'narche wears an eye patch? He had an accident when he was little, but it hasn't fazed him! Bless his heart.
        IN_THE_CHAOS_OF_WAR_THE_ARCHDUKE_HAD                                    = 10219,  -- In the chaos of war, the archduke had a brilliant plan. He believed that the three nations' only chance was to cast aside their squabbles and stand as one.
        EACH_NATION_HAD_TO_SHOULDER_AN_EQUAL_BURDEN                             = 10220,  -- Each nation had to shoulder an equal burden in the struggle against the beastmen. His strategy was truly brilliant!
        WITHOUT_HIS_GUIDANCE_THIS_WORLD_WOULD_HAVE_TURNED                       = 10221,  -- Without his guidance, this world would have turned to shadow under the domination of the beastmen.
        IN_THE_PAST_THERE_WAS_A_TERRIBLE_WAR                                    = 10222,  -- In the past, there was a terrible war. My father once told me how the earth, swept by furious winds, was soaked in the blood of the fallen.
        I_HEARD_HIS_TALES_EVERY_TIME_HE_DROWNED                                 = 10223,  -- I heard his tales every time he drowned his sorrows in drink. Now his stories are etched in my mind.
        SIR_WOLFGANG_S_FATHER_WAS_A_FAMOUS_SOLDIER                              = 10224,  -- Sir Wolfgang's father was a famous soldier, too. He commanded Jeuno's forces in the Crystal War, and his exploits are legendary.
        AFTER_THE_WAR_HE_LOOKED_AFTER_THE_FAMILIES                              = 10225,  -- After the war, he looked after the families of his fallen comrades. What a great man... There's more to being a soldier than just brute strength!
        SOMETIMES_I_SEE_THE_DARNDEST_THINGS_HERE_ONE                            = 10226,  -- Sometimes I see the darndest things here. One time, a rookie of ours got cursed in the necropolis of Eldieme, and I didn't know what to do.
        I_BET_THINGS_ARE_BREWING_THAT_ARE_WAY                                   = 10227,  -- I bet things are brewing that are way too crazy for us to imagine.
        ONCE_I_TOOK_A_NEW_GUY_TO_THE                                            = 10228,  -- Once I took a new guy to the Eldieme Necropolis, and he got cursed there. He went berserk, and had this unstoppable craving for raw meat.
        WELL_I_GAVE_IT_SOME_THOUGHT_AND_YOU                                     = 10229,  -- Well, I gave it some thought... And you know those torches in the rooms made of stone? Well, I heard that spirits hate them...
        SO_I_FIGURED_IT_MIGHT_HELP_IF_I                                         = 10230,  -- So, I figured it might help if I lit a lantern with those flames and brought it here. That's how we saved the guy.
        BUT_UH_I_VE_ALSO_HEARD_THAT_SOME                                        = 10231,  -- But, uh... I've also heard that some spirits actually like that kind of fire. So, it might not always be such a good idea.
        I_GUESS_WE_WERE_LUCKY_THEN_WE_HAD                                       = 10232,  -- I guess we were lucky then. We had no idea what else to do, and just wanted to do what we could.
        IF_YOU_WANT_WE_CAN_LEND_YOU_THE                                         = 10233,  -- If you want, we can lend you the lantern we used back then. What do you say?
        DO_YOU_WANT_TO_BORROW_THE_LANTERN_YES                                   = 10234,  -- Do you want to borrow the lantern? Yes, please. Not now.
        TRY_AND_BRING_BACK_THE_FLAMES_IN_THIS                                   = 10235,  -- Try and bring back the flames in this lantern. We don't know what else could help.
        I_SEEM_TO_REMEMBER_THERE_WERE_FOUR_TORCHES                              = 10236,  -- I seem to remember there were four torches, and that you had to light them in the proper order.
        YEAH_THAT_S_RIGHT_I_REMEMBER_SCREWING_THAT                              = 10237,  -- Yeah, that's right. I remember screwing that up. Too bad I forgot the real order, though. Well, I'm sure you can figure it out.
        DON_T_FORGET_IT_S_THE_STONE_WROUGHT                                     = 10238,  -- Don't forget it's the stone-wrought room that you're after. The torches in the caverns are for something else, so don't mix them up.
        OH_YEAH_WELL_YOU_RE_FREE_TO_USE                                         = 10239,  -- Oh, yeah? Well, you're free to use it any time.
        IF_YOU_KNEW_EXACTLY_WHICH_SPIRIT_IS_DOING                               = 10240,  -- If you knew exactly which spirit is doing the possessing, then you can figure out how to exorcise it. But that's the last resort, you know?
        OH_THE_FLAME_THING_DIDN_T_WORK_HUH                                      = 10241,  -- Oh, the flame thing didn't work, huh? Well, I'm just glad the spirit's gone!
        YEP_I_KNEW_IT_YOU_LEARN_SOMETHING_EVERY                                 = 10242,  -- Yep, I knew it. You learn something every day. I'm gonna write this up in the Guardsman's Daily.
        I_ALWAYS_WONDERED_HOW_SOMEONE_OF_HIS_HEIGHT                             = 10243,  -- I always wondered how someone of his height lit that lantern.
        THE_ARCHDUKE_HOSTS_SO_MANY_DIGNITARIES_EVERY_NIGHT                      = 10244,  -- The archduke hosts so many dignitaries, every night is a banquet. Composing original menus makes me fret!
        THIS_IS_THE_ARCHDUKE_S_CHAMBER_ONLY_HERE                                = 10245,  -- This is the archduke's chamber. Only here can he find refuge from his busy schedule...
        BUT_HE_S_ALWAYS_OUT_DOING_HIS_BEST                                      = 10246,  -- But he's always out, doing his best for the Duchy. We all look up to him so much. His deeds benefit not only Jeuno, but the entire world as well.
        ALL_I_CAN_DO_IN_RETURN_IS_CHANGE                                        = 10247,  -- All I can do in return is change his sheets and prepare hot soup.
        THESE_WORKS_ARE_PART_OF_LORD_EALD_NARCHE                                = 10248,  -- These works are part of Lord Eald'narche's collection. His Lordship is versed in history as well as art.
        THE_ARCHDUKE_AND_HIS_BROTHER_OFTEN_RELAX_IN                             = 10249,  -- The archduke and his brother often relax in this room. We always wait outside, but they do seem to get along quite well.
        I_DO_NOT_PRY_INTO_THEIR_CONVERSATIONS_BUT                               = 10250,  -- I do not pry into their conversations, but their knowledge of politics, culture, and philosophy rivals that of scholars.
        OUR_JOB_IS_TO_CONFRONT_ANYONE_SUSPICIOUS_WHY                            = 10251,  -- Our job is to confront anyone suspicious. Why, if anything happened to the archduke, the repercussions would be felt around the world.
        THIS_MONUMENT_WAS_BUILT_AT_THE_END_OF                                   = 10252,  -- This monument was built at the end of the war...as a reminder that nobody should suffer like that ever again.
        AND_NOW_PEOPLE_FORGET_THE_MISTAKES_OF_THE                               = 10253,  -- And now, people forget the mistakes of the past and quarrel all over again. I bet this is the only place where that promise is still remembered.
        I_WANT_SOMEBODY_TO_TAKE_THIS_MAP_I                                      = 10254,  -- I want somebody to take this map I got in the north and stave off impending disaster, but you don't look ready for such a task.
        MAYBE_YOU_CAN_TAKE_THIS_I_GOT_IN                                        = 10255,  -- Maybe you can take this % I got in the north, and stave off impending disaster... Do you think you've got what it takes?
        WHAT_DO_YOU_SAY_I_CAN_DO_IT                                             = 10256,  -- What do you say? I can do it. Not now.
        I_KNEW_YOU_WERE_THE_ONE_NOW_BRING                                       = 10257,  -- I knew you were the one! Now bring me % and show me what you're made of!
        WELL_THAT_S_A_BUMMER_I_THOUGHT_YOU                                      = 10258,  -- Well, that's a bummer. I thought you just might be the one!
        BRING_ME_I_M_COUNTING_ON_YOU                                            = 10259,  -- Bring me %. I'm counting on you!
        GOOD_JOB_I_KNEW_YOU_COULD_DO_IT                                         = 10260,  -- Good job! I knew you could do it. But be on your guard.
        DON_T_FORGET_OUR_VOW_HERE_REMEMBER_HOW                                  = 10261,  -- Don't forget our vow here. Remember how precious peace is.
        MMM_YOU_VE_ALREADY_GOT_ONE_WELL_THAT                                    = 10262,  -- Mmm? You've already got one. Well, that's great--think of it as a farewell present.
        GOOD_LUCK_WITH_THE_PETITION                                             = 10263,  -- Good luck with the petition!
        WELL_IF_THEY_CAN_TEAR_DOWN_THE_CLOCK                                    = 10264,  -- Well, if they can tear down the clock tower, who knows what they'll do to the monument? Quick, where do I sign?
        OH_DEAR_DID_YOU_LOSE_YOUR_WAY_I                                         = 10265,  -- Oh, dear... Did you lose your way? I didn't call for a cub like you.
        WELL_WELL_WELL_YOU_MIGHT_HAVE_WHAT_IT                                   = 10266,  -- Well, well, well... You might have what it takes. Hear me out. You've got nothing to lose.
        HEAR_ME_OUT_OKAY_ALL_RIGHT_NO_THANKS                                    = 10267,  -- Hear me out, okay? All right. No, thanks.
        OH_WHAT_A_PITY_GOODBYE                                                  = 10268,  -- Oh, what a pity. Goodbye.
        ALL_RIGHT_LOOK_THE_ARCHDUKE_S_RUNNING_LOW                               = 10269,  -- All right, look. The archduke's running low on food and gifts for all the foreign bigwigs he entertains.
        DON_T_YOU_THINK_SOMETHING_WEIRD_S_GOING                                 = 10270,  -- Don't you think something weird's going on? I mean, ambassadors from the three nations stop by all the time, and the train of delegates and caravans never stops.
        THE_REWARD_IS_REALLY_SOMETHING_IT_S_A                                   = 10271,  -- The reward is really something. It's a key the archduke himself found in the ruins. They say it makes things...automatically. Well? Wanna try it?
        WANNA_TRY_IT_YES_NO                                                     = 10272,  -- Wanna try it? Yes. No.
        GUESS_I_WAS_WRONG_ABOUT_YOU_BYE                                         = 10273,  -- Guess I was wrong about you. Bye.
        OH_NOW_YOU_RE_TALKIN_FIRST_PICK_OUT                                     = 10274,  -- Oh, now you're talkin'. First, pick out what you're going to collect from this list here.
        WHAT_TO_COLLECT_ACCESSORIES_FINE_SEAFOOD_RARE_HERBS                     = 10275,  -- What to collect? Accessories. Fine Seafood. Rare Herbs & Vegetables. Luxury Weapons and Armor. Exquisite Dishes. Exotic Medicines. Magical Instruments. Expensive Jewels. Quit.
        OKAY_SO_YOU_RE_GOING_TO_HAVE_TO                                         = 10276,  -- Okay, so you're going to have to collect %, %, %, and %.
        YOUR_REWARD_WILL_BE_WANNA_SEE_THE_OTHERS                                = 10277,  -- Your reward will be %. Wanna see the others?
        DO_YOU_WANT_TO_SEE_THE_OTHERS_YOU                                       = 10278,  -- Do you want to see the others? You bet. Not now.
        OKAY_SO_GOOD_LUCK_YOU_CAN_ONLY_HAVE                                     = 10279,  -- Okay. So, good luck! You can only have one chip for each element. They break when you use them, so come back if you want more.
        WHAT_YOU_DON_T_WANT_TO_DO_IT                                            = 10280,  -- What, you don't want to do it? All right. Just pick from this list, then.
        OKEY_DOKEY_NOT_TOO_SHABBY_THIS_IS_FOR                                   = 10281,  -- Okey-dokey. Not too shabby. This is for you!
        I_DON_T_KNOW_THE_DETAILS_BUT_YOU                                        = 10282,  -- I don't know the details, but you're supposed to take it to the ruins underground and put some mineral called ada-something in it. Well, come back anytime!
        NOW_OFFERING_QUICK_AND_EASY_DELIVERY_OF_PACKAGES                        = 10283,  -- Now offering quick and easy delivery of packages to homes everywhere!
        WOULD_YOU_CARE_TO_SEE_A_MAP_OF                                          = 10284,  -- Would you care to see a map of Greater Jeuno?
        WHAT_DO_YOU_SAY_SHOW_ME_NOT_NOW                                         = 10285,  -- What do you say? Show me. Not now.
        WE_STAND_IN_THE_GARDENS_OF_RU_LUDE                                      = 10286,  -- We stand in the gardens of Ru'Lude, at the very top of Jeuno's superstructure.
        A_MIGHTY_FINE_PALACE_THIS_IS_WHY_IT                                     = 10287,  -- A mighty fine palace, this is. Why, it's like a castle in the clouds! I'm so glad I came all this way to see it.
        OH_NOW_WHERE_D_THE_WIFE_HEAD_OFF                                        = 10288,  -- Oh, now where'd the wife head off to? I suppose she'll show up if I stay put here.
        I_GET_THE_CREEPS_LOOKING_DOWN_FROM_THE                                  = 10289,  -- I get the creeps looking down from the edge. It really hits you how high up we are.
        I_WONDER_HOW_THEY_MANAGED_TO_BUILD_THIS                                 = 10290,  -- I wonder how they managed to build this place? Jeuno's full of mysteries, like the airships! But the biggest one of all is the archduke. Nobody knows who he is or where he's from.
        I_HATE_YOU_ALL                                                          = 10291,  -- I hate you all!
        A_CLASSMATE_OF_MINE_ALWAYS_USED_TO_YELL                                 = 10292,  -- A classmate of mine always used to yell that whenever he climbed tall places. I wonder what he was trying to say?
        MY_HUSBAND_S_WANDERED_OFF_SOMEWHERE_RU_LUDE                             = 10293,  -- My husband's wandered off somewhere. Ru'Lude is so big, I'd better just wait for him here.
        YOU_CAN_SET_THIS_AS_YOUR_CURRENT_HOME                                   = 10294,  -- You can set this as your current home point. Once you set a home point, you will return there whenever you are incapacitated.
        SET_THIS_AS_CURRENT_HOME_POINT_YES_NO                                   = 10295,  -- Set this as current home point? Yes. No.
        HOME_POINT_SET                                                          = 10296,  -- Home point set!
        A_HOME_POINT_CAN_BE_SET_AS_A                                            = 10297,  -- A home point can be set as a spot for you to return to Vana'diel when you have been knocked out. You can also use a home point to teleport to other home points.
        WHAT_WILL_YOU_DO_TRAVEL_TO_ANOTHER_HOME                                 = 10298,  -- What will you do? Travel to another home point. Set this as your home point. Other settings. On second thought, never mind.
        YOU_HAVE_REGISTERED_A_NEW_HOME_POINT_YOU                                = 10299,  -- You have registered a new home point! You are now able to teleport here from any other home point.
        YOU_MAY_TELEPORT_FROM_HERE_TO_ANY_OTHER                                 = 10300,  -- You may teleport from here to any other home point you have registered.
        TELEPORT_WHERE_NEVER_MIND_PREVIOUS_PAGE_NEXT_PAGE                       = 10301,  -- Teleport where? Never mind. %. %. %. %. %. %. %. %. %. %. %. %. %. %. %. %. Previous page. Next page.
        TELEPORT_WHERE_J_NOWHERE_HOME_POINT_1_HOME                              = 10302,  -- Teleport where?%j Nowhere. Home Point #1[/ (M)/ (A)/ (E)]. Home Point #2[/ (M)/ (A)/ (E)]. Home Point #3[/ (M)/ (A)/ (E)]. Home Point #4[/ (M)/ (A)/ (E)]. Home Point #5[/ (M)/ (A)/ (E)].
        YOU_HAVE_NOT_YET_REGISTERED_ANY_OTHER_HOME                              = 10303,  -- You have not yet registered any other home points, and thus are unable to teleport.
        IT_COSTS_GIL_TO_TELEPORT_TO_HOME_POINT                                  = 10304,  -- It costs # gil to teleport to Home Point ## in %.
        THERE_IS_NO_FEE_FOR_TELEPORTING_TO_HOME                                 = 10305,  -- There is no fee for teleporting to Home Point ## in %.
        TELEPORT_CURRENT_GIL_YES_PLEASE_NO_THANK_YOU                            = 10306,  -- Teleport? (Current gil: #) [Add to favorites/Remove from favorites]. Yes, please. No, thank you.
        TELEPORT_TO_WHICH_REGION_ON_SECOND_THOUGHT_NONE                         = 10307,  -- Teleport to which region? On second thought, none. Select from favorites. Current region. [San d'Oria/Movalpolos]. [Bastok/Tavnazian Arch]. [Windurst/Lumoria]. [Jeuno/Mamool Ja Savage]. [Tavnazia/Halvung]. [West. Aht Urhgan/Arrapago Is]. [Adoulin Isles/Ruins of Alzadaal]. [Ronfaure/Ronfaure Front]. [Zulkheim/Norvallen Front]. [Norvallen/Gustaberg Front]. [Gustaberg/Derfland Front]. [Derfland/Sarutabaruta Front]. [Sarutabaruta/Aragoneu Front]. [Kolshushu/Fauregandi Front]. [Aragoneu/Valdeaunia Front]. [Fauregandi/East. Ulbuka]. [Valdeaunia/Ra'Kaznar]. [Qufim/]. [Li'Telor/]. [Kuzotz/]. [Vollbow/]. [Elshimo Low/]. [Elshimo Up/]. [Tu'Lia/]. Previous page. Next page.
        TELEPORT_WHERE_NONE_OF_THESE_A_FAVORITED_LOCATION                       = 10308,  -- Teleport where? None of these. A favorited location. An original area. A Rise of the Zilart area. A Chains of Promathia area. A Treasures of Aht Urhgan area. A Wings of the Goddess area. A Seekers of Adoulin area.
        YOU_MAY_CHANGE_THE_METHOD_OF_SELECTING_THE                              = 10309,  -- You may change the method of selecting the area of your desired home point to teleport to.
        WHICH_SETTING_WOULD_YOU_LIKE_MY_CURRENT_SETTING                         = 10310,  -- Which setting would you like? My current setting. Select by region. Select by expansion.
        YOU_ARE_NOW_SELECTING_BY                                                = 10311,  -- You are now selecting by [region/expansion].
        TELEPORT_WHERE_NONE_OF_THESE                                            = 10312,  -- Teleport where? None of these. % ##. % ##. % ##. % ##. % ##. % ##. % ##. % ##. % ##. [Add to favorites/Remove from favorites].
        HOME_POINT_IN_HAS_BEEN_YOUR_LIST_OF                                     = 10313,  -- Home Point ## in % has been [registered to/removed from] your list of favorite locations.
        YOUR_LIST_OF_FAVORITE_LOCATIONS_IS_FULL_YOU                             = 10314,  -- Your list of favorite locations is full. You must delete an existing entry in order to register a new one.
        DELETE_WHICH_NONE_OF_THESE                                              = 10315,  -- Delete which? None of these. % ##. % ##. % ##. % ##. % ##. % ##. % ##. % ##. % ##.
        WELCOME_TO_THE_AUCTION_HOUSE_DO_YOU_HAVE                                = 10316,  -- Welcome to the auction house. Do you have any questions about our establishment?
        WHAT_DO_YOU_WANT_TO_KNOW_WHAT_IS                                        = 10317,  -- What do you want to know? What is the auction house? How are auctions run? Are there any fees? Are there any limits? How do you check up on merchandise? How do you remove an item? My Sales Status list is full! Nothing right now.
        AUCTION_HOUSES_CAN_BE_FOUND_IN_ALL_OF                                   = 10318,  -- Auction houses can be found in all of Vana'diel's major cities. Here adventurers gather to bid on battle spoils, unwanted items, old armor...almost anything.
        CURRENTLY_THE_AUCTION_HOUSES_IN_BASTOK_SAN_D                            = 10319,  -- Currently, the auction houses in Bastok, San d'Oria, Windurst, and Jeuno all work independently. Therefore, prices differ from city to city.
        ADVENTURERS_MAY_USE_ANY_AUCTION_HOUSE_REGARDLESS_OF                     = 10320,  -- Adventurers may use any auction house regardless of nationality.
        THE_FIRST_ADVENTURER_TO_BID_AT_OR_ABOVE                                 = 10321,  -- The first adventurer to bid at or above the asking price will automatically purchase the product.
        ONCE_PUT_UP_FOR_AUCTION_MERCHANDISE_WILL_REMAIN                         = 10322,  -- Once put up for auction, merchandise will remain there for a maximum of thirty weeks Vana'diel time (nine-and-a-half days Earth time).
        IF_MERCHANDISE_DOES_NOT_SELL_WITHIN_THIS_TIME                           = 10323,  -- If merchandise does not sell within this time limit, it will be returned to the seller's current residence.
        TRANSACTION_FEES_ARE_PROPORTIONAL_TO_THE_AMOUNT_FOR                     = 10324,  -- Transaction fees are proportional to the amount for which an item is put up on auction. The method of calculating this fee is different for single items and stackable items.
        A_TRANSACTION_FEE_IS_COLLECTED_WHEN_ANY_MERCHANDISE                     = 10325,  -- A transaction fee is collected when any merchandise is put up for auction. This fee is nonrefundable.
