        HUH_YOU_RE_NOT_AFRAID_OF_AN_OLD                                         = 10488,  -- Huh? You're not afraid of an old man now, are you? Well, I guess I can give you a little more time to prepare. You can call it a handicap. Heh heh heh.
        SO_ARE_YOU_READY_TO_TAKE_ME_ON                                          = 10489,  -- So, are you ready to take me on?
        HEY_THAT_YOU_VE_GOT_THERE_IS_A                                          = 10490,  -- Hey, that % you've got there is a piece of junk. You'll need a new one if you want to fight me.
        LET_S_SEE_HOW_ABOUT_WE_DUEL_IT                                          = 10491,  -- Let's see... How about we duel it out [ /at Horlais Peak/at Balga's Dais/at Balga's Dais/at Horlais Peak/in the Waughroon Shrine/in the Waughroon Shrine/at the Qu'Bia Arena/at the Qu'Bia Arena/in the Waughroon Shrine/at the Qu'Bia Arena/at Horlais Peak/in the Chamber of Oracles/in the Chamber of Oracles/in the Chamber of Oracles/at Balga's Dais]? You know what to do with the % when you get there, right?
        NOW_IF_YOU_SHOW_ME_THAT_I_LL                                            = 10492,  -- Now if you show me that %, I'll even teleport you to the battlefield. Boy, are we going to have some fun!
        I_HAVE_TO_ADMIT_THAT_WAS_ONE_FINE                                       = 10493,  -- I have to admit, that was one fine display of fighting, %.
        IT_S_KIND_OF_HARD_TO_BELIEVE_BUT                                        = 10494,  -- It's kind of hard to believe, but did you know that Jeuno was once a run-down, tiny little fishing village?
        NOW_LOOK_AT_HER_THERE_ISN_T_A                                           = 10495,  -- Now look at her... There isn't a soul in Vana'diel who doesn't know her beauty. Let me tell you a story...
        LONG_AGO_THERE_WAS_A_YOUNG_MAN_CAPTAIN                                  = 10496,  -- Long ago, there was a young man--captain of a fishing boat, he was--who lived a modest life in the peaceful harbors of Jeuno. It was often hard for him to make ends meet, but he and his fishing buddies had no complaints. They loved their tiny village...
        HOWEVER_ONE_STORMY_NIGHT_FATE_CAME_KNOCKING_AT                          = 10497,  -- However, one stormy night, fate came knocking at his door when he rescued two strange lads from the nearby waters. From that day on, the wheels of change began to turn.
        THERE_WAS_SOMETHING_DIFFERENT_SOMETHING_SPECIAL_ABOUT_THOSE             = 10498,  -- There was something different--something special--about those two. They possessed a great deal of knowledge and leadership, and in just a short period of time, they transformed Jeuno from an insignificant dot on the map into a giant metropolis.
        AT_FIRST_THE_CAPTAIN_WELCOMED_THESE_CHANGES_WITH                        = 10499,  -- At first, the captain welcomed these changes with open arms. However, later he began to ask himself if all this was truly for the good of Jeuno, or if the city was just being used as a piece of some bigger plan put into motion by the two mysterious men...
        BUT_BY_THEN_IT_WAS_TOO_LATE_JEUNO                                       = 10500,  -- But by then it was too late... Jeuno and the people living within her walls had changed... There was no turning back.
        AND_SO_THE_CAPTAIN_DECIDED_WHILE_HE_STILL                               = 10501,  -- And so the captain decided: While he still had life inside his bones, he would make it his mission to remain and watch over his hometown.
        GOOD_DAY_MAAT                                                           = 10502,  -- Good day, Maat.
        OH_IF_IT_ISN_T_DOCTOR_MONBERAUX                                         = 10503,  -- Oh, if it isn't Doctor Monberaux.
        YOU_ARE_LOOKING_QUITE_HEALTHY_THESE_DAYS_OLD                            = 10504,  -- You are looking quite healthy these days, old chap.
        AS_HEALTHY_AS_A_HOBGOBLIN_THANKS_TO_YOUR                                = 10505,  -- As healthy as a Hobgoblin, thanks to your treatment. You sure know how to keep your patients happy, heh heh heh.
        HA_HA_I_M_JUST_DOING_MY_JOB                                             = 10506,  -- Ha ha. I'm just doing my job.
        BY_THE_WAY                                                              = 10507,  -- By the way...
        HM                                                                      = 10508,  -- Hm?
        YOU_MENTIONED_THIS_CAPTAIN_WATCHING_OVER_JEUNO_WHAT                     = 10509,  -- You mentioned this captain watching over Jeuno. What exactly was he making sure of?
        HMMM_WELL_HE_WAS_PROBABLY_JUST_MAKING_SURE                              = 10510,  -- Hmmm... Well, he was probably just making sure that everybody was happy.
        YOU_KNOW_I_THINK_YOU_ARE_PROBABLY_RIGHT                                 = 10511,  -- You know, I think you are probably right.
        THERE_ARE_MANY_THINGS_OUT_THERE_THAT_THREATEN                           = 10512,  -- There are many things out there that threaten the happiness of all Jeunoans, and he couldn't stand to sit back and watch that happiness be snatched away from them.
        MAAT                                                                    = 10513,  -- Maat...
        AHEM_AH_WILL_YOU_LOOK_AT_THE_TIME                                       = 10514,  -- Ahem. Ah, will you look at the time. I must be getting back to the infirmary. Take care, my friend.
        DON_T_YOU_WORRY_DOCTOR_I_ALWAYS_DO                                      = 10515,  -- Don't you worry, doctor. I always do. Oh, and you keep working on Wolfgang. Once he sees what's really going on in this place, he'll start to change. I know it...
        AS_DO_I                                                                 = 10516,  -- As do I...
        NOW_WHERE_WAS_I                                                         = 10517,  -- Now, where was I...
        AS_MUCH_AS_I_LONG_TO_SEE_IT                                             = 10518,  -- As much as I long to see it, it's likely I won't be around when the truth finally comes out. But young adventurers like you will. That's why I want you to be all that you can be.
        DO_NOT_FORGET_THE_HARDSHIPS_YOU_HAVE_ENDURED                            = 10519,  -- Do not forget the hardships you have endured to make it this far, and maybe one day you, too, will find something worth giving your life to protect.
        THEY_SAY_THAT_WHERE_THERE_IS_A_BEGINNING                                = 10520,  -- They say that where there is a beginning, there is an end. However, I believe that some things, like memories, don't have to end. That is where you young folk come in...
        AND_THAT_IS_ALL_THIS_SIMPLE_OLD_MAN                                     = 10521,  -- And that is all this simple old man can ask for...
        YOUR_LEVEL_LIMIT_IS_NOW_75                                              = 10522,  -- Your level limit is now 75.
        NOW_THAT_YOU_VE_REACHED_THE_STARS_THERE                                 = 10523,  -- Now that you've reached the stars, there's nothing left that I can do for you. Unless you'd like to go another round with a frail old man. If you're up to it, that is...
        WHEN_YOU_RE_READY_I_LL_BE_WAITING                                       = 10524,  -- When you're ready, I'll be waiting for you [ /at Horlais Peak/at Balga's Dais/at Balga's Dais/at Horlais Peak/in the Waughroon Shrine/in the Waughroon Shrine/at the Qu'Bia Arena/at the Qu'Bia Arena/in the Waughroon Shrine/at the Qu'Bia Arena/at Horlais Peak/in the Chamber of Oracles/in the Chamber of Oracles/in the Chamber of Oracles/at Balga's Dais]. Oh, and don't forget to bring along %.
        BUT_JUST_BECAUSE_I_M_OLD_DOESN_T                                        = 10525,  -- But just because I'm old doesn't mean I'm not a busy man. I don't need any half-hearted whippersnappers banging on my door, just to run off with their tails between their legs. If you want some thrill in your life, you had better be ready for the consequences! Heh heh heh!
        HEH_HEH_HEH_I_SEE_I_SEE_THAT                                            = 10526,  -- Heh heh heh. I see, I see... That just might work, kupo...
        AHEM_TOO_MUCH_TIME_AROUND_THESE_CRAZY_MOOGLES                           = 10527,  -- Ahem! Too much time around these crazy moogles and I just might turn into one!
        THE_WES_WORLD_EMIGRATION_SERVICE_IS_CURRENTLY_TAKING                    = 10528,  -- The WES (World Emigration Service) is currently taking applications for those who wish to immigrate to another World.
        WHEN_APPLYING_PLEASE_NOTE_THE_FOLLOWING                                 = 10529,  -- When applying, please note the following:
        YOU_CAN_ALWAYS_CANCEL_YOUR_EMIGRATION_DURING_THE                        = 10530,  -- You can always cancel your emigration during the application period by talking to any of the WES agents located conveniently about Vana'diel. However, once the period is over, you will no longer be able to cancel.
        AFTER_IMMIGRATING_TO_ANOTHER_WORLD_YOU_WILL_NOT                         = 10531,  -- After immigrating to another World, you will not be allowed to return to your previous World. Also, emigration is only allowed during periods when the WES is accepting applications.
        YOU_WILL_BE_UNABLE_TO_CHOOSE_THE_WORLD                                  = 10532,  -- You will be unable to choose the World to which you wish to emigrate. For more information on Worlds that we are accepting emigration applications for, please check the current PlayOnline news.
        IF_YOUR_CHARACTER_HAPPENS_TO_HAVE_THE_SAME                              = 10533,  -- If your character happens to have the same name as another player in the World to which you emigrate, you will have to change your name before entering that World.
        EMIGRATION_OF_CHARACTERS_IS_DONE_ONE_AT_A                               = 10534,  -- Emigration of characters is done one at a time.
        IF_YOU_REQUEST_EMIGRATION_FOR_ANY_OF_YOUR                               = 10535,  -- If you request emigration for any of your other characters, please conduct all applications separately.
        ALL_ITEMS_UP_FOR_AUCTION_AND_IN_YOUR                                    = 10536,  -- All items up for auction and in your Delivery Box will be lost when you emigrate. Please collect these items before moving.
        ANY_ITEMS_IN_YOUR_MOG_SAFE_WILL_BE                                      = 10537,  -- Any items in your Mog Safe will be transported with you to the new World.
        ANY_LINKSHELLS_LINKPEARLS_AND_PEARL_SACKS_WILL_BE                       = 10538,  -- Any linkshells, linkpearls, and pearl sacks will be destroyed at the time of emigration. However, linkshell owners will be presented with a new, unopened linkshell.
        FINALLY_ALL_MARKERS_PLACED_ON_YOUR_MAPS_WILL                            = 10539,  -- Finally, all markers placed on your maps will be erased.
        DO_YOU_WISH_TO_APPLY_FOR_EMIGRATION_YES                                 = 10540,  -- Do you wish to apply for emigration? Yes. No.
        YOUR_APPLICATION_FOR_WORLD_EMIGRATION_HAS_BEEN_ACCEPTED                 = 10541,  -- Your application for World emigration has been accepted!
        YOU_HAVE_ALREADY_SUBMITTED_AN_APPLICATION_FOR_EMIGRATION                = 10542,  -- You have already submitted an application for emigration.
        DO_YOU_WISH_TO_CANCEL_YOUR_APPLICATION_YES                              = 10543,  -- Do you wish to cancel your application? Yes. No.
        YOUR_APPLICATION_HAS_BEEN_CANCELED                                      = 10544,  -- Your application has been canceled!
        I_HAVE_BEEN_AUTHORIZED_TO_DISTRIBUTE_BRIDAL_WEAR                        = 10545,  -- I have been authorized to distribute bridal wear here. For details on wedding services, please read the PlayOnline news.
        HERE_IS_YOUR_SET_OF_BRIDAL_WEAR                                         = 10546,  -- Here is your set of bridal wear.
        WHICH_WORLD_WILL_YOU_EMIGRATE_TO_I_VE                                   = 10547,  -- Which world will you emigrate to? I've changed my mind. Bahamut Shiva Titan Ramuh Phoenix Carbuncle Fenrir Sylph Valefor Alexander Leviathan Odin Ifrit Diabolos Caitsith Quetzalcoatl Siren Unicorn Gilgamesh Ragnarok Next page.
        WHICH_WORLD_WILL_YOU_EMIGRATE_TO_I_VE_2                                 = 10548,  -- Which world will you emigrate to? I've changed my mind. Pandemonium Garuda Cerberus Kujata Bismarck Seraph Lakshmi Asura Midgardsormr Fairy Remora Hades Previous page.
        YOU_HAVE_ALREADY_SUBMITTED_AN_APPLICATION_FOR_EMIGRATION_2              = 10549,  -- You have already submitted an application for emigration to [Bahamut/Shiva/Titan/Ramuh/Phoenix/Carbuncle/Fenrir/Sylph/Valefor/Alexander/Leviathan/Odin/Ifrit/Diabolos/Caitsith/Quetzalcoatl/Siren/Unicorn/Gilgamesh/Ragnarok/Pandemonium/Garuda/Cerberus/Kujata/Bismarck/Seraph/Lakshmi/Asura/Midgardsormr/Fairy/Remora/Hades].
        YOUR_APPLICATION_FOR_EMIGRATION_TO_HAS_BEEN_ACCEPTED                    = 10550,  -- Your application for emigration to [Bahamut/Shiva/Titan/Ramuh/Phoenix/Carbuncle/Fenrir/Sylph/Valefor/Alexander/Leviathan/Odin/Ifrit/Diabolos/Caitsith/Quetzalcoatl/Siren/Unicorn/Gilgamesh/Ragnarok/Pandemonium/Garuda/Cerberus/Kujata/Bismarck/Seraph/Lakshmi/Asura/Midgardsormr/Fairy/Remora/Hades] has been accepted!
        AH_STANDING_HERE_IN_JEUNO_BRINGS_BACK_MEMORIES                          = 10551,  -- Ah, standing here in Jeuno brings back memories...
        TWENTY_YEARS_AGO_I_WORKED_IN_THIS_VERY                                  = 10552,  -- Twenty years ago, I worked in this very town with scientists from all over the world. We were trying to solve the hunger problem that plagued Vana'diel.
        WHAT_YOU_WANT_TO_HEAR_ABOUT_WHAT_HAPPENED                               = 10553,  -- What? You want to hear about what happened twenty years ago?
        TWENTY_YEARS_AGO_I_WORKED_IN_THIS_VERY_2                                = 10554,  -- Twenty years ago, I worked in this very town with scientists from all over the world. We were trying to solve the hunger problem that plagued Vana'diel.
        KORU_MORU_NOW_THAT_S_A_NAME_THAT                                        = 10555,  -- Koru-Moru! Now that's a name that brings back memories.
        PEOPLE_SAY_THAT_WE_SCIENTISTS_ARE_A_STRANGE                             = 10556,  -- People say that we scientists are a strange bunch, but Koru-Moru...now he was a crazy one.
        BUT_EVEN_A_WEIRD_ONE_LIKE_HIM_HAD                                       = 10557,  -- But even a weird one like him had a girl he loved. I'll never forget seeing him and Rasusu...
        YOU_SAY_YOU_RE_LOOKING_FOR_RASUSU_NOW                                   = 10558,  -- You say you're looking for Rasusu? Now why would a young lad/lass] like yourself want to do that?
        I_SEE_KORU_MORU_S_FINALLY_STARTED_TO                                    = 10559,  -- I see. Koru-Moru's finally started to remember... Well, that's one box of memories that should remain shut.
        IF_YOU_PROMISE_TO_KEEP_QUIET_ON_THE                                     = 10560,  -- If you promise to keep quiet on the subject, I'll tell you what I know.
        TWENTY_YEARS_AGO_THE_ROLANBERRY_FIELDS_WERE_RAMPAGED                    = 10561,  -- Twenty years ago, the Rolanberry Fields were rampaged by those dreadful Crawlers. The problem escalated to the point where the people of Jeuno had nothing to put on their dinner tables.
        ONE_ADVENTURER_SAW_THE_PROBLEM_THAT_LAY_BEFORE                          = 10562,  -- One adventurer saw the problem that lay before Jeuno and began calling for volunteers to travel to the Crawlers' Nest and exterminate the queen.
        SEEING_THAT_HER_RESEARCH_WAS_GOING_NOWHERE_RASUSU                       = 10563,  -- Seeing that her research was going nowhere, Rasusu decided to take her chances and go along with the adventurer.
        I_TRIED_TO_CONTACT_KORU_MORU_IN_HOPES                                   = 10564,  -- I tried to contact Koru-Moru, in hopes that I could get him to persuade Rasusu to stay in Jeuno. But at the same time, Windurst had its own problems, and I couldn't get ahold of him.
        AND_THEN_SHE_WENT_AND_NO_ONE_EVER                                       = 10565,  -- And then she went...and no one ever saw her again.
        AFTER_THE_WAR_ENDED_I_TRIED_WRITING_KORU                                = 10566,  -- After the war ended, I tried writing Koru-Moru many times, but I could never bring myself to tell him the truth about his beloved Rasusu.
        WINDURST_HAD_BEEN_DEVASTATED_BY_THE_GREAT_WAR                           = 10567,  -- Windurst had been devastated by the Great War, and Koru-Moru had seen the devastation with his own eyes. I could not bear to be the bringer of any more tragic news.
        KNOWING_KORU_MORU_THE_MEMORIES_OF_RASUSU_PROBABLY                       = 10568,  -- Knowing Koru-Moru, the memories of Rasusu probably got lost in the back of his tiny little head...
        YOU_KNOW_KORU_MORU_SO_YOU_CAN_UNDERSTAND                                = 10569,  -- You know Koru-Moru, so you can understand why I ask you to keep the truth from him--for his sake.
        TWENTY_YEARS_AGO_KORU_MORU_AND_RASUSU_WORKED                            = 10570,  -- Twenty years ago, Koru-Moru and Rasusu worked side by side for the good of Vana'diel.
        HOWEVER_THE_TERRIBLE_CRAWLERS_PULLED_THE_YOUNG_LOVERS                   = 10571,  -- However, the terrible Crawlers pulled the young lovers apart. A sad, sad story, it is.
        WHAT_IS_THIS_YOU_HAVE_FOUND_WHERE_DID                                   = 10572,  -- What is this you have found? %? Where did you get that?
        YOU_SAY_THAT_THIS_BELONGED_TO_RASUSU_THEN                               = 10573,  -- You say that this belonged to Rasusu? Then it is true. The poor soul perished in that infernal place...
        GOOD_LUCK_I_WILL_BESTOW_UPON_YOU_YOUR                                   = 10574,  -- Good luck, [citizen/comrade]. I will bestow upon you your nation's Signet.
        I_CANNOT_HELP_YOU_YOU_SHOULD_GO_FIND                                    = 10575,  -- I cannot help you. You should go find a guard from your own country.
        I_CANNOT_ACCEPT_CRYSTALS_FROM_SOMEONE_WHOSE_RANK                        = 10576,  -- I cannot accept crystals from someone whose rank is still 1. I advise you to either keep them until your reach rank 2, or to use them in craftwork.
        SINCE_WE_ARE_ALLIED_WITH_SAN_D_ORIA                                     = 10577,  -- Since we are allied with San d'Oria...
        SINCE_WE_ARE_ALLIED_WITH_BASTOK                                         = 10578,  -- Since we are allied with Bastok...
        SINCE_WE_ARE_ALLIED_WITH_WINDURST                                       = 10579,  -- Since we are allied with Windurst...
        I_AM_SORRY_I_AM_TOO_BUSY_WITH                                           = 10580,  -- I am sorry. I am too busy with other matters to be speaking with you.
        AH_YOU_HAVE_BROUGHT_US_SUPPLIES_THESE_WILL                              = 10581,  -- Ah, you have brought us supplies. These will help us indeed. I thank you.
        HMM_THESE_SUPPLIES_YOU_HAVE_BROUGHT_US_ARE                              = 10582,  -- Hmm... These supplies you have brought us are too old to be of any use. We will dispose of them promptly. I do commend you for your effort. May you succeed next time.
        YOU_VE_EARNED_CONQUEST_POINTS                                           = 10583,  -- You've earned conquest points!
        YOU_VE_RECEIVED_YOUR_NATION_S_SIGNET_YOU                                = 10584,  -- You've received your nation's Signet. You are now taking part in your nation's conquest campaign!
        I_AM_A_TEMPLE_KNIGHT_I_AM_ONE                                           = 10585,  -- I am , a Temple Knight. I am one of the guards charged with overseeing San d'Oria's conquest campaign.
        I_AM_AN_IRON_MUSKETEER_I_AM_ONE                                         = 10586,  -- I am , an Iron Musketeer. I am one of the guards charged with overseeing Bastok's conquest campaign.
        I_AM_A_WAR_WARLOCK_I_AM_ONE                                             = 10587,  -- I am , a War Warlock. I am one of the guards charged with overseeing Windurst's conquest campaign.
        WHAT_IS_YOUR_BUSINESS_WOULD_YOU_CAST_SIGNET                             = 10588,  -- What is your business? Would you cast Signet on me? I want to spend my conquest points. [I want to join the Expeditionary Force./Teleport me to the E.F. area.] I want to quit the E.F./change my E.F. I want to go on a supplies quest. I have some questions... Nothing, sorry to bother you.
        WHAT_DO_YOU_WISH_TO_KNOW_ABOUT_NOTHING                                  = 10589,  -- What do you wish to know about? Nothing. Conquests. Conquest results. Donating crystals. Conquest points. The effects of controlling regions. Regions controlled by other nations. Regions under beastman control.
        ALL_THREE_NATIONS_ARE_STRIVING_DAILY_TO_PUT                             = 10590,  -- All three nations are striving daily to put more regions under their control. This is what we call conquests. You can take part in it and serve your country by defeating enemies while you have Signet cast on you.
        EACH_REGION_COMPRISES_SEVERAL_AREAS_AND_THE_NATION                      = 10591,  -- Each region comprises several areas, and the nation that rids those areas of the most monsters gains control of the region.
        NATIONS_RECEIVE_GOODS_AND_RESOURCES_FROM_REGIONS_UNDER                  = 10592,  -- Nations receive goods and resources from regions under their control.
        SO_THE_MORE_REGIONS_WE_CONTROL_THE_RICHER                               = 10593,  -- So, the more regions we control, the richer our nation becomes.
        BORDER_GUARDS_ARE_ALSO_PLACED_IN_OUTPOSTS_WITHIN                        = 10594,  -- Border guards are also placed in outposts within regions under our control. They are there to cast Signet on adventurers like yourself.
        ONCE_YOU_HAVE_YOUR_NATION_S_SIGNET_YOU                                  = 10595,  -- Once you have your nation's Signet, you will be able to acquire crystals from enemies you defeat.
        NOT_ONLY_THAT_BUT_YOU_WILL_ALSO_RECEIVE                                 = 10596,  -- Not only that, but you will also receive conquest points. You get more conquest points if you defeat enemies in regions that are not under your nation's control. These points can be used to purchase items from guards like myself.
        SO_YOU_SEE_CONQUESTS_BENEFIT_NATIONS_AND_ADVENTURERS                    = 10597,  -- So you see...conquests benefit nations and adventurers alike. We expect you to do your best to serve your country.
        YOU_CAN_SEE_THE_CURRENT_STATE_OF_CONQUESTS                              = 10598,  -- You can see the current state of conquests by selecting Region Info from the main menu. Conquest results in all regions are regularly recalculated, so you may want to check them from time to time.
        SHOPS_IN_OUR_CITY_WILL_BE_SELLING_DIFFERENT                             = 10599,  -- Shops in our city will be selling different items according to our conquest rank. The Troupe Valeriano will also visit the nation that finishes first and bring a little joy to its citizens.
        YOU_CAN_DONATE_CRYSTALS_TO_YOUR_NATION_ONCE                             = 10600,  -- You can donate crystals to your nation once you achieve rank 2. Just trade them to guards like myself, and we will ensure they are sent to the proper place.
        WE_WOULD_LIKE_YOU_TO_DONATE_CRYSTALS_TO                                 = 10601,  -- We would like you to donate crystals to your nation from now on. Just trade them to guards like myself, and we will ensure they are sent to the proper place.
        YOU_CAN_ACQUIRE_CRYSTALS_BY_DEFEATING_ENEMIES_WHILE                     = 10602,  -- You can acquire crystals by defeating enemies while you have your nation's Signet. Having Signet cast on you is also the only way of taking part in conquests.
        RANK_POINTS_WILL_BE_AWARDED_TO_YOU_FOR                                  = 10603,  -- Rank points will be awarded to you for each crystal you donate, and you may be offered new missions as your rank goes up.
        YOU_ALSO_RECEIVE_RANK_POINTS_FOR_COMPLETING_MISSIONS                    = 10604,  -- You also receive rank points for completing missions. Complete missions and take part in conquests to raise your rank and serve your country.
        YOU_ARE_AWARDED_CONQUEST_POINTS_WHEN_YOU_DEFEAT                         = 10605,  -- You are awarded conquest points when you defeat monsters while you are taking part in conquests. Select "Region Info" from the menu to check your current number of conquest points.
        YOU_CAN_PURCHASE_ITEMS_FROM_GUARDS_LIKE_MYSELF                          = 10606,  -- You can purchase items from guards like myself with your conquest points, but be warned that the number of points you spend will be subtracted from your current total.
        WHEN_CONQUEST_RESULTS_ARE_ANNOUNCED_YOU_WILL_BE                         = 10607,  -- When conquest results are announced, you will be told which country controls the region you are in at that time. Sometimes regions may become neutral, or beastmen may even gain control of regions.
        IF_WE_GAIN_CONTROL_OF_A_REGION_BORDER                                   = 10608,  -- If we gain control of a region, border guards will be placed at its outposts to help adventurers like you.
        MERCHANTS_WILL_ALSO_BE_PLACED_THERE_AND_GOODS                           = 10609,  -- Merchants will also be placed there, and goods from that region will find their way to the local shops here.
        GAINING_CONTROL_OF_REGIONS_IS_THE_BASIC_PRINCIPLE                       = 10610,  -- Gaining control of regions is the basic principle behind conquests. We need each of you to do your best, and bring our nation to the top of the ranks.
        OF_COURSE_SOMETIMES_WE_LOSE_REGIONS_TO_OTHER                            = 10611,  -- Of course, sometimes we lose regions to other nations...so we must try to take them back before the next conquest results are announced.
        AS_AN_INCENTIVE_WE_WILL_AWARD_YOU_WITH                                  = 10612,  -- As an incentive, we will award you with more conquest points for defeating monsters in those regions.
        BUT_IF_WE_ARE_ALLIED_WITH_ANOTHER_NATION                                = 10613,  -- But if we are allied with another nation, you will only be awarded the regular rate for defeating monsters in our allies' regions. On the other hand, we will award you with more points for fighting in the top-ranked nation's regions.
        OUR_PARAMOUNT_CONCERN_LIES_IN_THE_BEASTMEN_GAINING                      = 10614,  -- Our paramount concern lies in the beastmen gaining control of our regions. If too many of us are defeated in a region, the beastmen will gain control of it.
        IF_THIS_HAPPENS_NOT_ONLY_IS_IT_A                                        = 10615,  -- If this happens, not only is it a great blow to our pride, but you will be unable to acquire any crystals in that region.
        THE_BEASTMEN_ARE_A_MENACE_TO_ALL_NATIONS                                = 10616,  -- The beastmen are a menace to all nations. If they rise to power, we must all unite and drive those vile creatures from that region.
        WE_NEED_YOU_TO_BRING_SUPPLIES_TO_THE                                    = 10617,  -- We need you to bring supplies to the outpost border guards who are placed in regions under our control.
        THERE_IS_ONE_OUTPOST_IN_EACH_REGION_SELECT                              = 10618,  -- There is one outpost in each region. Select Region Info from the menu, and look for the areas with a small flag mark on the map. That is where they are.
        HERE_ARE_THE_SUPPLIES_JUST_GIVE_THEM_TO                                 = 10619,  -- Here are the supplies. Just give them to the guard at the outpost and your mission will be complete. Now, choose which outpost you want to go to. We give different rewards for each region, so choose carefully.
