        S_LJ_HJ_YZOPE_3_K_YZ_S                                                  = 14395,  -- %S%LJ]hj%[ yzOPe|3?; %K yz@s[ubh yzhbOm[Y yzbL[}CX^[ yzs %eJ-6 yznw[k yzoX^[Y~N yz[hoU[ yzG[XXv#^[ yzN#X^ %SJon %SJoff yz&J=f%i
        ID                                                                      = 14396,  -- ID:
        ID_TAB                                                                  = 14397,  -- ID_TAB:
        TAB_AREA                                                                = 14398,  -- TAB_AREA:
        WHAT_BRINGS_YOU_TO_THE_DUCHY_WEARING_SUCH                               = 14399,  -- %. What brings you to the Duchy wearing such a grave expression?
        I_SEE_4                                                                 = 14400,  -- ...I see.
        NEEDLESS_TO_SAY_IT_IS_BEYOND_MY_STATION                                 = 14401,  -- Needless to say, it is beyond my station to render a decision on affairs of state. Wait here. I will consult with my superiors.
        IT_IS_AS_I_EXPECTED_THE_DUCHY_WILL                                      = 14402,  -- It is as I expected. The Duchy will hold formal deliberations as to the potential repercussions of our involvement in this matter.
        CHIN_UP_THE_EARNESTNESS_OF_THE_EMPIRE_S                                 = 14403,  -- Chin up, %. The earnestness of the Empire's plea has not been lost on our diplomats. Perhaps the Silent Empire truly intends to change its ways...
        I_CAN_OFFER_NO_PROMISES_BUT_ENCOURAGE_YOU                               = 14404,  -- I can offer no promises, but encourage you to do what you can in the meantime.
        YOU_MAKE_FOR_THE_THREE_NATIONS_FROM_HERE                                = 14405,  -- You make for the three nations from here, do you not? Then be on your way, and have faith that good tidings will await you upon your return.
        HAVE_YOU_RECEIVED_CONSENT_FROM_THE_THREE_NATIONS                        = 14406,  -- Have you received consent from the three nations? Not yet, you say? Then I suggest you get moving.
        THE_SEALS_OF_THE_THREE_NATIONS_YES_EVERYTHING                           = 14407,  -- The seals of the three nations...yes, everything seems to be in order. Good work.
        YOU_LL_BE_PLEASED_TO_KNOW_THAT_THE                                      = 14408,  -- You'll be pleased to know that the Duchy has also agreed to give its consent. Here are the relevant papers.
        I_TRUST_YOU_LL_SEE_THAT_THIS_MATTER                                     = 14409,  -- I trust you'll see that this matter ends well for all of us, %. Now you'd best be on your way.
        YOU_THERE_YES_YOU_ADVENTURER_YOUR_DOWNCAST_COUNTENANCE                  = 14410,  -- You there. Yes, you, adventurer! Your downcast countenance tells me your life wants for exhilaration.
        WHO_AM_I_YOU_ASK_LET_S_JUST                                             = 14411,  -- Who am I, you ask? Let's just say I'm he who is about to banish all trace of tedium from your life with an irresistible offer--one of otherworldly proportions, to be sure. For a mere # gil, this % I hold is yours.
        BUT_WHAT_IN_SLUMBERING_SAMWELL_S_SHANK_DOES                             = 14412,  -- But what in Slumbering Samwell's shank does it do, you ask? Consider yourself fortunate, for it's my policy to demystify before the customer buys.
        WHAT_WILL_YOU_DO_LET_HIM_RAMBLE_PURCHASE                                = 14413,  -- What will you do? Let him ramble. Purchase %. Learn how to use it. Discard abyssite. Leave.
        AHEM_ALLOW_ME_TO_PRESENT_YOU_WITH_A                                     = 14414,  -- Ahem! Allow me to present you with a supposition.
        LYING_IN_PARALLEL_TO_THE_WORLD_UPON_WHICH                               = 14415,  -- Lying in parallel to the world upon which we stand exists another dimension.
        ABYSSEA_IS_ITS_NAME_OR_AT_LEAST_THE                                     = 14416,  -- Abyssea is its name--or at least, the name I've bestowed upon it. It is a world of boundless beauty, mystique, and riches unclaimed.
        NOW_SUPPOSE_THIS_I_HOLD_IS_A_KEY                                        = 14417,  -- Now, suppose this % I hold is a key to accessing Abyssea. Were you in possession of one, your curiosity would get the better of you, yes?
        STRICTLY_SPEAKING_THIS_OBJECT_DOES_NOT_GRANT_ENTRY                      = 14418,  -- Strictly speaking, this object does not grant entry into Abyssea itself.
        IT_DOES_HOWEVER_MAKE_IT_POSSIBLE_TO_INTERACT                            = 14419,  -- It does, however, make it possible to interact with beings from that plane of existence--Abysseans, I call them.
        THE_SERVES_TO_DETECT_ABYSSEANS_THAT_WANDER_THE                          = 14420,  -- The % serves to detect Abysseans that wander the gulf between worlds. How those hapless creatures--I refer to them as Voidwalkers--found their way there, mind you, is another subject entirely.
        HAVING_DRIFTED_TO_THIS_REALM_FROM_THE_WORLD                             = 14421,  -- Having drifted to this realm from the world yonder, much like the Voidwalkers themselves, % are attuned to the presence of these creatures and will react--vibrate and emit light--when they draw near.
        THE_CLOSER_YOUR_DISTANCE_TO_A_VOIDWALKER_THE                            = 14422,  -- The closer your distance to a Voidwalker, the stronger the reaction becomes, until the creature is forcibly wrested into this dimension.
        REPEATED_CONTACT_WITH_ABYSSEANS_WILL_CAUSE_THE_TO                       = 14423,  -- Repeated contact with Abysseans will cause the % to take on different hues, allowing it to respond to creatures belonging to the higher echelons of Voidwalkers.
        BE_FOREWARNED_ABYSSEANS_ARE_AMONG_THE_MOST_FOUL                         = 14424,  -- Be forewarned! Abysseans are among the most foul-tempered, unpredictable creatures. You would do well to steel yourself for a trying encounter prior to making contact.
        I_TRUST_YOUR_MANY_ADVENTURES_HAVE_MADE_YOU                              = 14425,  -- I trust your many adventures have made you familiar with those ghastly statues scattered across the land called cavernous maws.
        MY_OBSERVATIONS_HAVE_REVEALED_THAT_THE_CONCENTRATION_OF                 = 14426,  -- My observations have revealed that the concentration of Voidwalkers is greatest in locations where these statues are found.
        AS_YET_I_HAVE_NO_PLAUSIBLE_EXPLANATIONS_FOR                             = 14427,  -- As yet, I have no plausible explanations for this phenomenon, but you needn't concern yourself with such details.
        YOURS_MY_FRIEND_IS_A_DILEMMA_INFINITELY_SIMPLER                         = 14428,  -- Yours, my friend, is a dilemma infinitely simpler in nature.
        ALL_THIS_FAR_FETCHED_TALK_OF_ABYSSEA_ABYSSEANS                          = 14429,  -- All this far-fetched talk of Abyssea, Abysseans, and Voidwalkers...
        I_M_FULLY_AWARE_OF_THE_FANTASTICAL_NATURE                               = 14430,  -- I'm fully aware of the fantastical nature of my tale, and do not think poorly of those inclined to skepticism.
        YET_I_FEEL_NO_NEED_TO_VOUCH_FURTHER                                     = 14431,  -- Yet I feel no need to vouch further for the authenticity of my claims. Such is my confidence that the truth speaks for itself.
        NOW_THEN_A_GREAT_NEW_WORLD_HAS_PRESENTED                                = 14432,  -- Now then. A great new world has presented itself before you. The question is, will you embrace this opportunity, or let it pass you by?
        AS_ABYSSEANS_CROSS_FROM_ONE_REALM_TO_ANOTHER                            = 14433,  -- As Abysseans cross from one realm to another, so too does gil pass from one individual to the next. In my mind, it is only fitting that gil is that which grants you the key to Abyssea.
        MY_TALES_HAVE_PIQUED_YOUR_INTEREST_HAVE_THEY                            = 14434,  -- My tales have piqued your interest, have they? As I have mentioned prior, the price is # gil.
        HAND_OVER_GIL_AYE_NAY                                                   = 14435,  -- Hand over # gil? Aye. Nay.
        NO_THE_SUM_I_ASK_IS_BY_NO                                               = 14436,  -- No? The sum I ask is by no means prohibitive. I'll be waiting here, should you ever change your mind.
        I_THANK_YOU_FOR_YOUR_CUSTOM_HERE_IS                                     = 14437,  -- I thank you for your custom. Here is your very own %!
        AS_A_SERVICE_FOR_ALL_CUSTOMERS_UPON_REQUEST                             = 14438,  -- As a service for all customers, upon request I will take your % off your hands and dispose of it in your stead.
        THE_ABILITY_TO_MEDDLE_WITH_INTER_DIMENSIONAL_MATTER                     = 14439,  -- The ability to meddle with inter-dimensional matter can be considered a great power, with which comes great responsibility. Indeed there have been those who found the burden beyond their capacity to cope.
        IT_SEEMS_YOU_ARE_SHORT_ON_GIL_YET                                       = 14440,  -- It seems you are short on gil. Yet I cannot grant concessions, lest access to otherworldly realms lose its true value.
        I_SEE_YOU_VE_DEVELOPED_A_TASTE_FOR                                      = 14441,  -- I see you've developed a taste for %. Yet I fear I cannot furnish you further, for one alone is sufficient to invite misfortune upon the heedless.
        YOU_WISH_TO_KNOW_HOW_TO_USE_THE                                         = 14442,  -- You wish to know how to use the %? There is no trick to it. Allow me to demonstrate.
        WHILE_IN_POSSESSION_OF_SIMPLY_ASSUME_A_RESTING                          = 14443,  -- While in possession of %, simply assume a resting pose. I'm given to understand it is second nature to all adventurers.
        DOING_SO_WILL_CAUSE_YOUR_TO_REACT_PERTINENT                             = 14444,  -- Doing so will cause your % to react. Pertinent information can be gleaned by observing the magnitude of its vibration and the manner of light emitted.
        SHOULD_NEITHER_REACTION_OCCUR_TAKE_IT_TO_MEAN                           = 14445,  -- Should neither reaction occur, take it to mean that no Voidwalkers roam the area.
        SHOULD_IT_VIBRATE_SOFTLY_BUT_EMIT_NO_LIGHT                              = 14446,  -- Should it vibrate softly but emit no light, take it to mean that Voidwalkers have recently passed through and may soon return.
        SHOULD_IT_VIBRATE_SOFTLY_AND_EMIT_A_GENTLE                              = 14447,  -- Should it vibrate softly and emit a gentle light, take it to mean that Voidwalkers presently roam the area.
        NOW_PAY_PARTICULAR_ATTENTION_TO_WHAT_I_M                                = 14448,  -- Now, pay particular attention to what I'm about to explain. The reaction of the % will change once a predetermined distance from a Voidwalker has been closed.
        FROM_THAT_POINT_ONWARDS_THE_MAGNITUDE_OF_THE                            = 14449,  -- From that point onwards, the magnitude of the vibration corresponds directly to the creature's strength. Based on this knowledge, it is your decision whether to pursue it further.
        THE_GENTLE_GLOW_OF_LIGHT_ON_THE_OTHER                                   = 14450,  -- The gentle glow of light, on the other hand, will intensify to become a radiant beam pointing in the direction of the creature.
        FOLLOWING_THAT_BEAM_TO_ITS_END_WILL_CAUSE                               = 14451,  -- Following that beam to its end will cause the heretofore invisible Voidwalker to cross fully over into this world and take form.
        THIS_PRECISE_MOMENT_OF_ENCOUNTER_WITH_AN_ABYSSEAN                       = 14452,  -- This precise moment of encounter with an Abyssean, I have dubbed contact.
        NOT_ONLY_ARE_ABYSSEANS_KNOWN_TO_BE_TEMPERAMENTAL                        = 14453,  -- Not only are Abysseans known to be temperamental and unpredictable; there are those that demonstrate a degree of cunning and guile far beyond that seen in this world.
        CONSIDER_YOURSELF_WARNED                                                = 14454,  -- Consider yourself warned.
        FOR_AS_SURELY_AS_THE_BEAM_OF_LIGHT                                      = 14455,  -- For as surely as the beam of light emitted by the % guides you to a Voidwalker, so too does it guide the Voidwalker to you. Be ever mindful of this fact.
        KNOW_ALSO_THAT_NOT_ONE_BUT_NUMEROUS_VOIDWALKERS                         = 14456,  -- Know also that not one, but numerous Voidwalkers may roam the land at any given time, and the readings indicate only the creature nearest you.
        YOU_WOULD_DO_WELL_TO_CHECK_THE_READINGS                                 = 14457,  -- You would do well to check the readings regularly, as a sudden change in the light's direction could mean a different Voidwalker has wandered your way.
        VOIDWALKERS_WILL_ONLY_REVEAL_THEIR_TRUE_FORM_AT                         = 14458,  -- Voidwalkers will only reveal their true form at the point of contact, and seeking one only to be met with another is a scenario all adventurers want to avoid.
        BUT_SURELY_YOU_GROW_WEARY_OF_MY_RAMBLINGS                               = 14459,  -- But surely, you grow weary of my ramblings. I for one believe this is something best learned through doing.
        HAS_THE_BURDEN_OF_THIS_RESPONSIBILITY_PROVEN_TOO                        = 14460,  -- Has the burden of this responsibility proven too heavy to bear? Very well, I will take it off your hands and see to its disposal.
        DISCARD_WHICH_ONE_NONE_OF_THEM                                          = 14461,  -- Discard which one? % % % % % % % % % % None of them.
        ARE_YOU_CERTAIN_AYE_NAY                                                 = 14462,  -- Are you certain? Aye. Nay.
        IT_IS_DONE_YOU_NEEDN_T_CONCERN_YOURSELF                                 = 14463,  -- It is done. You needn't concern yourself with unseen foes any longer. A tame, tranquil adventuring life bereft of exhilaration will be yours once more.
        FORGIVE_ME_MY_PERSONAL_THIRST_FOR_THE_UNKNOWN                           = 14464,  -- Forgive me. My personal thirst for the unknown has no bearing on the decisions of others. I will be here, however, should you have a change of heart.
        GIL_PAID_OBTAINED_KEY_ITEM                                              = 14465,  -- # gil paid. Obtained key item: %!
        YOU_RELINQUISH_THE                                                      = 14466,  -- You relinquish the %.
        KUPO_HO_ANOTHER_ADVENTURER_HAS_FOUND_HIS_HER                            = 14467,  -- Kupo-ho! Another adventurer has found his/her] way to my domain. Was it my aura of superior sagacity that led you here? This conspicuous crate and chest that sit seductively at my side?
        MANY_SECRETS_HAVE_I_TO_TELL_BUT_SADLY                                   = 14468,  -- Many secrets have I to tell, but sadly, they would be beyond your meager mental faculties to fathom. Return when your abilities are up to the task.
        IT_IS_NO_MATTER_WHAT_MATTERS_IS_THAT                                    = 14469,  -- It is no matter. What matters is that you are here, and from the look of it, you are a suitable subject for the task I would entrust to you.
        I_SPEAK_TO_YOU_ON_BEHALF_OF_THE                                         = 14470,  -- I speak to you on behalf of the Magian Mooglehood, an ancient and august assembly of wisemoogles hailing from the once-glorious Kingdom of Kupalika.
        OUR_PREDECESSORS_WERE_COUNCILORS_AND_CONFIDANTS_TO_NONE                 = 14471,  -- Our predecessors were councilors and confidants to none other than the celebrated King Kupofried himself. To this day, it is our mission to safeguard the secrets of their moogle magic and see them properly passed down to posterity.
        EACH_ILLUSTRIOUS_MEMBER_OF_THE_MAGIAN_MOOGLEHOOD_GUARDS                 = 14472,  -- Each illustrious member of the Magian Mooglehood guards knowledge of a distinct branch of our lineal lore. My specialty lies in weaponry; with my aid, you will be doling out damage and destruction in ways heretofore unimagined!
        WHAT_IMPELLED_YOU_TO_IMPART_THIS_LONG_WITHHELD                          = 14473,  -- What impelled you to impart this long-withheld wisdom to us? And why now, kupo? the unenlightened adventurer might ask.
        TO_WHICH_THE_WISE_MOOGLE_WOULD_READILY_REPLY                            = 14474,  -- To which the wise moogle would readily reply: The answer, my friend, is in the mog tablets--those remarkable relics wrought by King Kupofried himself--that were only recently recovered by resourceful adventurers such as rrr...yourself.
        THERE_IS_AN_ANCIENT_AND_SOMEWHAT_ALARMING_PROPHECY                      = 14475,  -- There is an ancient (and somewhat alarming) prophecy in our mooglehood. It goes...<ahem>...King Kupofried's creations shall slumber soundly until such time as their Super Kupowers are called upon to save the realm from utter ruin, kupo.
        THE_PARTICULARS_OF_THE_PROPHECY_PREPOSTEROUS_AS_THIS                    = 14476,  -- The particulars of the prophecy--preposterous as this may seem--outstrip even our prodigious powers of perception.
        YET_THIS_I_KNOW_KUPO_IF_MOOGLE_MAGIC                                    = 14477,  -- Yet this I know, kupo: if moogle magic is what shall deliver this world from destruction, then moogle magic this world shall have--in abundance!
        AS_AN_ADVENTURER_OF_RENOWN_REPUTE_AND_PARAMOUNT                         = 14478,  -- As an adventurer of renown, repute, and paramount prowess, you would seem a worthy beneficiary for our boon. And yet the Magian Mooglehood is nothing if not meticulously methodical. No, we must be certain...
        I_PROPOSE_TO_TASK_YOU_WITH_A_SERIES                                     = 14479,  -- I propose to task you with a series of trials. Each time you emerge victorious, we shall proffer you a portion of our powers, kupo.
        WHAT_SAY_YOU_ADVENTURER_WILL_YOU_UNDERTAKE_THE                          = 14480,  -- What say you, adventurer? Will you undertake the Trial of the Magians, that you might one day wield the mightiest of moogle magic to save your realm from destruction and devastation?
        TACKLE_THE_TRIAL_OF_THE_MAGIANS_KUPO_WILL                               = 14481,  -- Tackle the Trial of the Magians, kupo? Will I ever! Maybe another time...
        EXCELLENT_THEN_MY_FIRST_GIFT_UNTO_YOU_SHALL                             = 14482,  -- Excellent. Then my first gift unto you shall be this: a journal that shall serve to record all of your extraordinary exploits.
        WE_UNDERSTAND_FOR_WITH_GREAT_KUPOWER_COMES_GREAT                        = 14483,  -- We understand, for with great kupower comes great responsibility. Should you ever be willing to bear the burden, we shall welcome your return.
        YOU_WHO_WOULD_INHERIT_THE_MYSTERIES_OF_THE                              = 14484,  -- You, who would inherit the mysteries of the magians...speak unto me your wish, kupo.
        CHOOSE_YOUR_ACTION_REVIEW_CURRENT_TRIAL_ABANDON_CURRENT                 = 14485,  -- Choose your action: Review current trial. Abandon current trial. List available trials. Ask for aid. Ask about roaming trial log. Move on.
        WHICH_TRIAL_TRIAL_TRIAL_TRIAL_TRIAL_TRIAL_TRIAL                         = 14486,  -- [Review/Abandon] which trial? Trial #. Trial #. Trial #. Trial #. Trial #. Trial #. Trial #. Trial #. Trial #. Trial #. Return.
        YOU_ARE_NOT_CURRENTLY_UNDERTAKING_ANY_TRIALS                            = 14487,  -- You are not currently undertaking any trials.
        TARGET_ITEM_PRE_AUGMENTATION                                            = 14488,  -- Target item (pre-augmentation): %.
        TARGET_ITEM_POST_AUGMENTATION                                           = 14489,  -- Target item (post-augmentation): %.
        PRESS_ONWARD_WITH_THIS_TRIAL_PERSEVERE_RETIRE                           = 14490,  -- Press onward with this trial? Persevere. Retire.
        ABANDON_THIS_TRIAL_AND_ALL_RECORDS_OF_YOUR                              = 14491,  -- Abandon this trial, and all records of your efforts thus far will be lost forever. I encourage due deliberation before making your decision.
        TRULY_ABANDON_THE_TRIAL_KUPO_PERSEVERE_RETIRE                           = 14492,  -- Truly abandon the trial, kupo? Persevere. Retire.
        VERY_WELL_KUPO_I_SHALL_REMOVE_ALL_RECORDS                               = 14493,  -- Very well, kupo. I shall remove all records of this trial from your %.
        YOU_HAVE_ABANDONED_TRIAL                                                = 14494,  -- You have abandoned Trial #.
        REMEMBER_THAT_BEFORE_YOU_CAN_UNDERTAKE_A_NEW                            = 14495,  -- Remember that before you can undertake a new trial, your target item must be purged of its trial insignia.
        TRADE_THE_ITEM_TO_ME_AND_I_SHALL                                        = 14496,  -- Trade the item to me, and I shall see it returned to its pristine original state, kupo.
        YOU_ARE_NOT_CURRENTLY_UNDERTAKING_THAT_TRIAL                            = 14497,  -- You are not currently undertaking that trial.
        KUPO_HO_THIS_ITEM_BEARS_THE_INSIGNIA_OF                                 = 14498,  -- Kupo-ho. This item bears the insignia of a trial already abandoned.
        IT_IS_BUT_A_SUPERFLUOUS_SCRIBBLE_NOW_SHALL                              = 14499,  -- It is but a superfluous scribble now. Shall I erase it for you, kupo?
        ERASE_THE_ABANDONED_TRIAL_INSIGNIA_YES_REMOVE_IT                        = 14500,  -- Erase the abandoned trial insignia? Yes, remove it. No, leave it.
        KUPO_HO_MY_MOOGLE_MAGIC_SEEMS_TO_HAVE                                   = 14501,  -- Kupo...ho? My moogle magic seems to have misfired. Perhaps we should try that again.
        THE_TRIAL_INSIGNIA_HAS_VANISHED_FROM_YOUR                               = 14502,  -- The trial insignia has vanished from your %.
        SELECT_A_CATEGORY_HAND_TO_HAND_DAGGERS_SWORDS                           = 14503,  -- Select a category: Hand-to-Hand. Daggers. Swords. Great Swords. Axes. Great Axes. Scythes. Polearms. Katana. Great Katana. Clubs. Staves. Archery. Marksmanship. Instruments. Search by trial number. Cancel.
        KUPO_HO_HO_I_KNOW_OF_NO_SUCH                                            = 14504,  -- Kupo-ho...ho? I know of no such trial. And given the immense nature of my intellect, that means it could not possibly exist.
        WHAT_WOULD_YOU_KNOW_KUPO_ABOUT_THE_TRIALS                               = 14505,  -- What would you know, kupo? About the trials. Undertaking a trial. Completing a trial. Return.
        DID_I_NOT_REGALE_YOU_WITH_THE_TALE                                      = 14506,  -- Did I not regale you with the tale of the magians only a short while ago? Well, not all can be possessed of moogle-class powers of memory...
        AS_I_HAVE_ALREADY_APPRISED_YOU_THE_ANCIENT                              = 14507,  -- As I have already apprised you, the ancient moogle art of weapon augmentation is my specialty, kupo.
        FIRST_YOU_MUST_RETRIEVE_A_WEAPON_FROM_THE                               = 14508,  -- First, you must retrieve a weapon from the chest beside me. Show it to me, and I will reveal to you the trials you may undertake to receive my boon.
        THE_I_ENTRUSTED_TO_YOU_WILL_RECORD_YOUR                                 = 14509,  -- The % I entrusted to you will record your exploits for up to ten trials at any given time, kupo.
        BE_AWARE_THAT_CERTAIN_EXTRAORDINARY_WEAPONS_ENTAIL_EXCLUSIVE            = 14510,  -- Be aware that certain extraordinary weapons entail exclusive trials. Such details and more may be confirmed by requesting of me a list of available trials.
        SHOULD_YOU_SUCCESSFULLY_COMPLETE_AN_ASSIGNED_TRIAL_RETURN               = 14511,  -- Should you successfully complete an assigned trial, return and present your target weapon to me to substantiate your success.
        IF_I_DEEM_THAT_YOU_HAVE_COMPLETED_MY                                    = 14512,  -- If I deem that you have completed my challenge in good order, you shall receive your reward right then and there, kupo!
        NOW_THIS_IS_IMPORTANT_ENOUGH_THAT_I_SHALL                               = 14513,  -- Now, this is important enough that I shall say it twice, even thrice: at the end of your trial, you must trade to me the very same weapon you submitted at the start.
        LOSE_THIS_WEAPON_AND_ALL_YOUR_HARD_WON                                  = 14514,  -- Lose this weapon and all your hard-won successes will be for naught. You must avoid such a grievous gaffe at all costs, kupo.
        VERY_WELL_SHOW_ME_THE_TARGET_WEAPON_FOR                                 = 14515,  -- Very well. Show me the target weapon for the trial of which you speak, kupo.
        KUPO_HO_IS_THAT_I_SEE_WHY_YES                                           = 14516,  -- Kupo-ho! Is that % I see? Why, yes... I could fashion a fitting trial or two for you, kupo.
        ARE_YOU_ABSOLUTELY_POSITIVELY_SURE_THAT_YOU_WANT                        = 14517,  -- Are you absolutely, positively sure that you want to undertake Trial #, kupo?
        UNDERTAKE_TRIAL_I_AM_READY_PERHAPS_ANOTHER_TIME                         = 14518,  -- Undertake Trial #? I am ready. Perhaps another time.
        EXCELLENT_KUPO_NOW_TO_INVOKE_A_SIMPLE_INCANTATION                       = 14519,  -- Excellent, kupo! Now, to invoke a simple incantation, and...
        YOUR_IS_NOW_RECORDING_THE_PROGRESS_OF_YOUR                              = 14520,  -- Your % is now recording the progress of your trials!
        THROUGH_THE_MARVEL_OF_MOOGLE_MAGIC_YOUR_EXPLOITS                        = 14521,  -- Through the marvel of moogle magic, your exploits will be recorded without you having to so much as lift a quill! And just in case you're the forgetful type...
        A_TRIAL_INSIGNIA_HAS_BEEN_INSCRIBED_UPON_YOUR                           = 14522,  -- A trial insignia has been inscribed upon your %!
        NOTE_YOU_MAY_NOT_UNDERTAKE_A_DIFFERENT_TRIAL                            = 14523,  -- Note: You may not undertake a different trial with an already-inscribed weapon.
        KUPO_OH_MIGHT_YOUR_MIND_BE_MUDDLED_MY                                   = 14524,  -- Kupo-oh? Might your mind be muddled, my friend? You're already attempting that trial.
